GXTreeLayoutAlgorithm - Class in btdebuggertool.simulator
A layout algorithm that spreads the directed graph as a tree from top down first a root is chosen (we offer a default way that may be overridden) then a tree is first spread from that root down in a grid fashion after which it is laid out bottom up to horizontally shift nodes.
